                    <span>OpenSSL is a terrific programming resource, but the online documentation on it<BR>is hard to understand and index. This book brings most of it all together, and<BR>provides enough examples to answer most of your questions.<P>One thing that it lacks is tie-ins with Java; most of its examples are in Perl <BR>and Python. I'm currently trying to see if certain ideas can be implemented in Java.<P>A great book, and great read!</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">THE best book out on the OpenSSL...</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
